not grant an open-source license or any right of use beyond what
is set out below.


1. What is permitted

  (a) Reading the source, browsing on GitHub, and forking within
      GitHub for the sole purpose of proposing changes back to
      this repository through a pull request.


2. What is NOT permitted

  (a) Cloning the source and building an executable to use in
      place of the free edition (distributed on GitHub Releases)
      or the paid edition (distributed on the Microsoft Store)
      that BrightRyo publishes. This is prohibited by the MOJIOKO
      End User License Agreement §3.10.

  (b) Modifying the code to bypass the free-vs-paid feature
      gating (for example, the isPackagedAsMsix flag or any
      resource that gates access to paid-edition features or
      fonts) and using the resulting build for any purpose. This
      is prohibited by the MOJIOKO End User License Agreement
      §3.9.

  (c) Redistributing the source, a modified version of the
      source, or any executable built from the source, to any
      third party, whether for consideration or free of charge.
      This is prohibited by the MOJIOKO End User License
      Agreement §3.3 and §3.4.

  (d) Treating this repository as if it were licensed under an
      OSI-approved open-source license (MIT, Apache-2.0, GPL, and
      similar). No such licence is granted here.


3. Binary editions and the EULA

The binary editions distributed by BrightRyo — the free edition on
GitHub Releases (linked from https://brightryo.github.io/mojioko/)
and the paid edition on the Microsoft Store
(https://apps.microsoft.com/detail/9N03JMH9LF6M) — are governed by
the MOJIOKO End User License Agreement bundled with each release
at build/license_en.txt (English) / build/license_ja.txt
(Japanese). The prohibitions in section 2 above are stated for
repository-root visibility, but the authoritative text lives in
the EULA.


4. Third-party components

Third-party libraries, fonts, and other assets bundled with the
Software carry their own licences, which are documented in
installer/licenses/README.md. Where a third-party licence and this
statement conflict, the third-party licence prevails.


5. Enquiries

  GitHub Issues: https://github.com/brightryo/mojioko/issues


